<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870715-0132 </DOCNO><HL> Financing Business:Chariot Group Inc.</HL><DD> 07/15/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CGR </IN><TEXT>   CHARIOT GROUP INC., based in Sandusky, Ohio, said it arranged a $17.5 million line of credit with Cleveland-based Banc One Corp.'s Bank One unit. Chariot, formerly known as Sandusky Plastics Inc., said it will use the credit line to repay certain debt and to finance new equipment, among other things. Chariot makes plastic containers, cabinetry and aluminum doors and windows. </TEXT></DOC>